40|$|Proactive {{secret sharing}} deals with {{refreshing}} secret shares, i. e., redistributing {{the shares of}} a secret to the original <b>access</b> <b>structure.</b> In this paper {{we focus on the}} general problem of redistributing shares of a secret key. Shares of a secret have been distributed such that access sets specified in the <b>access</b> <b>structure</b> G (e. g., t-out-of-l) can access (or use) the secret. The problem is how to redistribute the secret, without recovering it, {{in such a way that}} those specified in the new <b>access</b> <b>structure</b> G' will be able to recover the secret. We also adapt our scheme such that it can be used in the context of threshold cryptography and discuss its applications to secure databases...|$|R
